column16:
* Each Area in "PopulationSettlementsLocations2023" layer is subdivided into many Hara units (Census boundaries).
* (Harah) is a part of the city that includes a group of buildings, streets, and roads. It has a well-known name and is often surrounded by main streets that separate it from other neighborhoods. Neighborhoods have been given numbers at the city level, starting with the number 001 and ending with the number of the last neighborhood in the city.
* Could be more useful in the Settlement Level analysis compared to the "PopulationSettlementsLocations2023" layer

column5: The seismicity datapoint  layer for the Al-Jouf region (AlJouf Seismicity) covering the period from 1999 to 2025 includes essential details for each seismic event, such as the date and time of occurrence, depth, the magnitude value (MAGNITU), in addition to monitoring accuracy indicators and associated error metrics. This data is a crucial tool for assessing seismic hazards and studying the tectonics of the region.

column5: Strong Motion data focuses on measuring intense, near-field ground shaking resulting from large-magnitude earthquakes that have significant engineering implications. This data is recorded by specialized instruments called Accelerographs, which activate effectively when a certain acceleration threshold is exceeded

Weak Motion data represents the continuous recordings of low-amplitude seismic waves, collected by highly sensitive Broadband monitoring stations. Its purpose is the early and accurate detection of all levels of seismic activity, and the precise determination of earthquake source characteristics, including location, magnitude, and depth. This data is the cornerstone of geophysical and tectonic studies, contributing to the understanding of fault mechanisms, developing models of the Earth's internal structure, and defining the general seismic hazard of a region.

column5: A point layer representing the locations of hydrogeological wells. This layer precisely delineates the spatial coordinates for each well and incorporates critical hydrogeological attributes, specifically the Static Water Level (S.W.L.), Dynamic Water Level (D.W.L.), and well depth, thereby enabling robust spatial analysis of the hydraulic characteristics pertinent to the water-bearing formations within the Al-Jouf region.
